41
00:04:59,201 --> 00:05:00,896
Incredible...

42
00:05:00,937 --> 00:05:04,338
to be the first Walczak
to graduate from college.

43
00:05:09,445 --> 00:05:11,743
Think fast.

44
00:05:13,115 --> 00:05:15,140
There's a gift in both,
but you only get to choose one.

45
00:05:15,184 --> 00:05:16,913
Dad, come on.

46
00:05:16,953 --> 00:05:18,682
That's not fair.

47
00:05:18,721 --> 00:05:21,622
Nobody said life was fair.

48
00:05:25,394 --> 00:05:27,021
You're 25 now.

49
00:05:27,063 --> 00:05:29,156
I'm offering you a deal.

50
00:05:29,198 --> 00:05:32,031
Your first demolition project
on your own.

51
00:05:32,068 --> 00:05:34,332
And if you succeed,

52
00:05:34,370 --> 00:05:36,861
you are longer
my employee.

53
00:05:36,906 --> 00:05:39,306
- You'll be my partner.
- (applause)

54
00:05:39,342 --> 00:05:42,778
Dad, this is really important
for me.

55
00:05:42,812 --> 00:05:46,646
Don't you wanna see
what's in the blue one?

56
00:05:49,285 --> 00:05:51,617
For those,

57
00:05:51,654 --> 00:05:54,020
well, I got a little help
from Peter.

58
00:05:54,056 --> 00:05:57,651
Three weeks touring
the architectural wonders of Europe.

59
00:05:57,693 --> 00:05:59,217
It's always been
your dream, right?

60
00:05:59,261 --> 00:06:02,697
And they're for two.

61
00:06:09,939 --> 00:06:12,669
Sam:
I have a friend who hunts.

62
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:14,767
He'll track a deer for miles,

63
00:06:14,810 --> 00:06:18,337
totally quiet,
waiting for the right shot.

64
00:06:18,381 --> 00:06:21,817
And if his aim is dead on
and the deer goes down,

65
00:06:21,851 --> 00:06:25,810
he says he gets the biggest rush
of his life.

66
00:06:25,855 --> 00:06:28,790
That's how I feel
when taking down a building...

67
00:06:28,824 --> 00:06:31,588
studying blueprints,
exploring structure,

68
00:06:31,627 --> 00:06:34,824
drawing up demo plans,
placing the ammunition.

69
00:06:37,099 --> 00:06:38,828
That's all foreplay to me.

70
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:54,208
Pete, are you jealous?

71
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:56,775
Pete: Well, lucky for me,
Malestrazza's not alive

72
00:06:56,819 --> 00:06:58,650
or I would be jealous.

73
00:06:58,688 --> 00:07:00,588
Sam:
Okay, I've passed the sign.

74
00:07:00,623 --> 00:07:03,683
- Pete: It should be right there.
- No, I don't see it yet.

75
00:07:05,061 --> 00:07:07,689
People still live there,
huh?

76
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:10,756
Yeah, according to your father.

77
00:07:11,834 --> 00:07:14,394
Here it is.

78
00:07:14,437 --> 00:07:16,928
- Hello.
- Sam, I can't hear you.

79
00:07:16,972 --> 00:07:18,963
- Hello.
- Hello.

80
00:08:23,239 --> 00:08:25,503
Can I help you?

81
00:08:25,541 --> 00:08:29,272
Hi, I'm from Walczak,
the demolition company.

82
00:08:29,311 --> 00:08:32,678
I wasn't expecting you
so soon.

83
00:08:35,050 --> 00:08:36,347
Are you alone?

84
00:08:36,385 --> 00:08:39,183
Yeah, for now.

85
00:08:42,258 --> 00:08:43,384
Jimmy!

86
00:08:48,330 --> 00:08:51,026
I'm Mary Sutter.
I take care of the building.

87
00:08:51,066 --> 00:08:52,624
Did Mr. Collins tell you

88
00:08:52,668 --> 00:08:55,694
the nearest hotel
is 50 miles away?

89
00:08:55,738 --> 00:08:57,729
Yeah, but it might be easier
if I just stay here.

90
00:08:57,773 --> 00:09:00,742
Oh, good.

91
00:09:18,861 --> 00:09:20,385
Where were you?

92
00:09:20,429 --> 00:09:22,897
Just playing
with the dog, Mom.

93
00:09:22,932 --> 00:09:24,490
Don't worry.

94
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:27,730
This is the lady
we were expecting.

95
00:09:27,770 --> 00:09:29,829
Already?

96
00:09:29,872 --> 00:09:32,238
So why don't you show her around,
explain the rules

97
00:09:32,274 --> 00:09:35,471
and set her up
in room 208?

98
00:09:39,782 --> 00:09:41,875
And be polite.

99
00:09:49,959 --> 00:09:51,688
Do you smoke?

100
00:09:51,727 --> 00:09:53,854
- Well, sometimes.
- No smoking in the building.

101
00:09:53,896 --> 00:09:57,423
Those are the rules.

102
00:09:59,435 --> 00:10:02,962
So this place is
in pretty good shape, considering.

103
00:10:03,005 --> 00:10:06,031
Yeah, Mom likes
to keep everything spotless.

104
00:10:06,075 --> 00:10:08,168
She's kind of crazy.

105
00:10:14,016 --> 00:10:17,952
Can we...
can we get the lights back on?

106
00:10:23,792 --> 00:10:25,760
The lights go off
every six minutes,

107
00:10:25,794 --> 00:10:28,262
you know,
to save electricity and stuff.

108
00:10:28,297 --> 00:10:31,892
If you spend a day in the halls,
you have to hit the switch 240 times.

109
00:10:31,934 --> 00:10:35,199
Oh, and never go
on the eighth floor.

110
00:10:35,237 --> 00:10:38,172
- That's Malestrazza's floor.
- The architect lived here?

111
00:10:38,207 --> 00:10:41,005
That's the only floor
Mom doesn't clean.

112
00:10:41,043 --> 00:10:43,136
It's in the rules.

113
00:10:45,915 --> 00:10:48,748
Oh, and another rule...
don't go on the roof.

114
00:10:48,784 --> 00:10:51,480
It's too dangerous.

115
00:10:54,256 --> 00:10:55,951
Here it is.

116
00:10:55,991 --> 00:10:58,357
Home sweet home.

117
00:11:08,871 --> 00:11:10,998
What do you think he'll say?

118
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:14,168
- Sorry.
- Malestrazza.

119
00:11:14,209 --> 00:11:16,973
When he finds out you've come
to blow up his building.

120
00:11:21,216 --> 00:11:25,209
Hello, Peter.
Yeah, it's insane.

121
00:11:25,254 --> 00:11:27,449
I mean, imagine something
from Gotham City

122
00:11:27,489 --> 00:11:30,151
in the middle
of a freakin' marshland.

123
00:11:30,192 --> 00:11:32,092
Malestrazza was
definitely a genius.

124
00:11:32,127 --> 00:11:34,561
This building's amazing.

125
00:11:34,596 --> 00:11:38,430
It's like the Bates Motel,
only bigger.

126
00:11:38,467 --> 00:11:40,230
You know,
the kid who still lives here,

127
00:11:40,269 --> 00:11:43,568
he talks about Malestrazza
like he's still...

128
00:11:43,605 --> 00:11:46,870
hey, hello?

129
00:11:46,909 --> 00:11:48,900
(beep)

130
00:12:06,161 --> 00:12:09,096
(girl whispering)
Samantha!

131
00:12:10,866 --> 00:12:14,597
(gasps, coughs)

132
00:12:24,113 --> 00:12:26,104
(whirring)

133
00:12:33,822 --> 00:12:36,347
(indistinct voices)

134
00:12:57,346 --> 00:12:59,541
(tapping sound)

135
00:13:10,325 --> 00:13:12,259
(footsteps)

136
00:13:18,367 --> 00:13:20,130
Hello?

137
00:13:20,169 --> 00:13:22,933
- (gasps)
- Oh, I'm sorry.

138
00:13:22,971 --> 00:13:24,939
I didn't realize
you were here.

139
00:13:24,973 --> 00:13:27,840
Do you like red wine?

140
00:13:30,412 --> 00:13:32,141
I also brought some bread

141
00:13:32,181 --> 00:13:34,911
and some pasta, some tea.

142
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:36,975
It's not much,
but it should do for tonight.

143
00:13:37,019 --> 00:13:38,350
Thanks, Miss Sutter.

144
00:13:38,387 --> 00:13:42,118
No, please, call me Mary.

145
00:13:42,157 --> 00:13:45,354
So how many people
still live here?

146
00:13:45,394 --> 00:13:48,727
Only four.

147
00:13:48,764 --> 00:13:50,527
And this apartment?

148
00:13:50,566 --> 00:13:53,467
I'd offer to move you to another,
but this is the only vacant one

149
00:13:53,502 --> 00:13:56,164
- that hasn't been emptied.
- No, it's okay.

150
00:13:56,205 --> 00:13:59,197
It's just the last tenants,
why did they leave all their stuff?

151
00:13:59,241 --> 00:14:03,041
Because no one
came to collect it.

152
00:14:07,216 --> 00:14:09,207
Do you know the history
of this building?

153
00:14:09,251 --> 00:14:11,151
No, why?

154
00:14:11,186 --> 00:14:14,883
Perhaps it's best
you just do your job then.

155
00:14:17,159 --> 00:14:19,354
Good night.

156
00:14:22,598 --> 00:14:24,793
Sam:
November 12, 2008,

157
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:27,734
demolition report
number 2893.

158
00:14:27,769 --> 00:14:31,364
Originally designed and constructed
by one Joseph Malestrazza,

159
00:14:31,406 --> 00:14:34,102
the building contains eight
individual levels

160
00:14:34,143 --> 00:14:37,874
housing 120 residential units.

